column1: #Text=The latest maintenance of MDO has been migrated to [LiUSemWeb/Materials-Design-Ontology](https://github.com/LiUSemWeb/Materials-Design-Ontology).
#Text=MDO is an ontology for materials design field, representing the domain knowledge specifically related to solid-state physics and computational materials science.
#Text=### What does Materials Design Ontology consist of?
#Text=Materials Design Ontology consists of 4 modules which are:
#Text=* [Core](https://w3id.org/mdo/core/1.0): This module consists of the top-level concepts and relationships of the materials design ontology, which are also reused in other modules
#Text=* [Structure](https://w3id.org/mdo/structure/1.0): The structure module is intended to represent the structural information of materials.
#Text=Such structural information is also the basis of materials calculations
#Text=* [Calculation](https://w3id.org/mdo/calculation/1.0): This module is intended to represent the classification of different computational methods
#Text=* [Provenance](https://w3id.org/mdo/provenance/1.0): This module is intended to represent the provenance information of materials data and calculation
#Text=* A full MDO importing all the above modules is avaliable at [MDO Full](https://w3id.org/mdo/full/1.0).
#Text=Li H, Armiento R, Lambrix P, "An Ontology for the Materials Design Domain", [published version](https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-3-030-62466-8_14) (accepted at ISWC 2020)
